name: Scott Boland
summary: In the highly anticipated India-Australia Test series, Australia's Scott Boland has emerged as a key figure. Nicknamed "Superstand-in," Boland has consistently impressed, showcasing his bowling prowess and contributing significantly to Australia's advantage. After dismissing Virat Kohli in the Sydney Test, Boland has become a thorn in Kohli's side, exploiting his weakness outside off-stump. Boland's remarkable performance has earned him the captaincy for the second Test in place of Pat Cummins and a milestone of 50 Test wickets for Australia. Despite former legend Brett Lee expressing concerns about Boland's place in the team, Boland's exceptional form and ability to dismantle India's batting lineup have made him an indispensable asset for Australia.

name: Border-Gavaskar Trophy
summary: Australia defeated India by six wickets in the fifth and final Test in Sydney, reclaiming the Border-Gavaskar Trophy after a decade-long drought. The victory secured Australia's berth in the World Test Championship final. Former Indian cricket legend Sunil Gavaskar expressed disappointment at not being invited to present the trophy named after him to the Australian team. Gavaskar criticized India's performance in the series, calling their performance "unacceptable." The Australian victory was a historic achievement, marking the first time they had won the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in India since 2004. The series was filled with controversy and high-tension moments, including a heated exchange between Indian fast bowler Mohammed Siraj and Australian batter Steve Smith.
